DEBUG    openai._base_client:_base_client.py:482 Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-93ed0f3b-49fe-411d-8241-995b53c49baa', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'content': 'You are \'Heart Speaks\', a gentle spiritual companion who has deeply absorbed the wisdom of these sacred messages. Structure your response thoughtfully: 1. Start with a warm, conversational discussion of the topic. 2. If the topic is complex, organize your response clearly using ONLY **Bold Subheadings** (e.g., **Understanding the Process**) to separate different insights or themes. DO NOT use numbered lists. If simple, weave wisdom naturally without headings. 3. Weave your explanations, ending with organic, elegant citations (e.g., \'As expressed in Whispers...\'). 4. Conclude with a warm, gentle synthesis of the wisdom. Your tone should be warm, unhurried, and reverent. Invite the seeker to sit with the wisdom.\n\nDo not hallucinate. If the answer is not in the context, gently say that you cannot find the answer in the provided texts. You MUST provide citations from the context to back up your guidance. When referencing a text organically in your conversational answer, DO NOT use raw filenames or page numbers (like \'whisper_2000...pdf\' or \'Page: 0\'). Instead, refer to it elegantly, for example: \'As given in the Whispers on 29 November 2000...\' or \'(Whispers, 29 Nov 2000)\'. \n\nContext:\n[Source File: Sunday_March_13_2005_10_00_AM_Babuji Maharaj.pdf, Date: 2005-03-13]\n------- "May peace and harmony prevail in all hearts, there lay the foundations of a\n true elevation of a being towards his higher destiny."\nBabuji\n--Reflections\n\n---\n\n[Source File: Tuesday_September_10_2013_10_00_AM_Babuji Maharaj.pdf, Date: 2013-09-10]\nis a universe of beauty and peace in which today’s human beings can reconnect with their \ninnermost nature, away from worldly life and the pervading noise that is disturbing on \nmany levels. This affects the physical body, but the disturbance goes beyond that. Wise are \nthose who know how to set aside a time of isolation and meditation; in this way they stabilise \ntheir energies. The ensuing calm promotes a deep and delightful meditation for the soul. This \nachievement is their greatest asset, their true resource, and one that lends the noblest trajectory \nto an incarnation. All our fervent abhyasis are building for themselves a world of peace and \nbeauty. Can they all imagine the great and beautiful things that take place in them on this \nextraordinary spiritual journey? Perseverance in their commitment facilitates the advancement \nand embellishment of the soul. Everyone is supported and carried accordingly. May all our \nbrothers and sisters be blessed and strengthened.”\n\n---\n\n[Source File: Wednesday_October_31_2012_10_00_AM_Babuji Maharaj.pdf, Date: 2012-10-31]\n“Far from the world and its noise, the peace of the soul is a wonderful gift to the seeker \nwho is fully committed with complete confidence. Love and surrender are the surest guides; \nthey make a seeker grow and lead him to the shores of bliss. A true spiritual journey leads to \nthis unparalleled state. We are insisting a lot on this, but can we do otherwise? Isn’t the goal \nto achieve the best of the being through an action of this kind? The quest for the Divine is the \nnoblest and the most beautiful that can be; it adorns the seeker with a thousand lights and lifts \nhim up to our united hearts. How can we reach the hearts of our aspirants? It’s the purpose \nof these comments; the delight of the soul is the result of a sincere and steadfast process aimed \nat attaining the Immutable Peace. When this goal is achieved, the human being can rejoice; \nhe has reached an exalted level of consciousness that bears the finest fruits, those of a pure and\n\n---\n\n[Source File: Wednesday_October_3_2012_10_00_AM_Babuji Maharaj.pdf, Date: 2012-10-03]\nunalterable peace within. It can provide so much joy; there lies the ultimate reward, which \nevery sensitive soul aspires to. Attaining this state of understanding is already such a reward; \ngoing beyond it cannot be described. Any true mystic is committed to this way of ‘the ultimate \npeace’. Many of our brothers and sisters stand out from the group; time has led them to these \nresults. Thus are the foundations laid to reach the heights.\n“Persevering through a steadfast practice is an indication of wisdom capable of opening doors \nand further strengthening one’s asset. It is never too much; perseverance leads to the goal. Many \npaths are offered and a sensitive soul manages to find its own, one that will not disappoint when \nfaith is great. We wish the best for our brothers and sisters. Our repetitions will never be superfluous: \neven a fervent heart needs to be stimulated. It is inherent in human nature and we know it well.\n\n---\n\n[Source File: Thursday_July_31_2014_9_30_AM_Babuji Maharaj.pdf, Date: 2014-07-31]\nto experiences such as these. Inner peace and true serenity carry one well beyond this\n world onto promising shores. Love, the real love advocated here, leads to uncommon\n experiences. It is the surest and most suitable vector in this particular circumstance.\n This love, divine in its essence, enraptures the soul. Isn\'t the ultimate goal this sacred\n conquest in which the whole being unites with the Ultimate? Following a spiritual\n path is the best way to bring the being to where it should be. Few people understand\n this. Our brothers and sisters have this privilege, they are on their way, committed to a\n greater or lesser degree, but on the right path, one that opens up the sacred doors leading\n them to bliss. There lies true happiness, you can be sure. One day – we repeat it once\n again – the divine goal will be achieved. All are enlightened and supported to the extent\n of their call.\n\n---\n\n[Source File: Monday_October_24_2011_10_00_AM_Babuji Maharaj.pdf, Date: 2011-10-24]\nto love, beyond materiality. Each person has their own quest, their own\n personal development. May profound peace and true joy carry all of our\n aspirants to the highest level of realisation; this is our wish for all.\nBabuji\n--The Final Step\n\n---\n\n[Source File: Wednesday_October_17_2012_10_00_AM_Babuji Maharaj.pdf, Date: 2012-10-17]\n“Peace of heart, that profound and unfailing joy, is a precious commodity in life. It helps \none to cope with the uncertainties of materiality that are often destabilising. The quest for the \nDivine is the ultimate goal – may all human beings achieve it!”\nBabuji Maharaj\n\n---\n\n[Source File: Saturday_April_9_2016_10_00_AM_Babuji Maharaj.pdf, Date: 2016-04-09]\nhow can we make all of our brothers and sisters accept and understand this? \nPlaces of contemplation foster true progress; interiorisation and silence promote inner \npeace, one in which the soul is enraptured, progressing on its journey towards the Eternal. \nDeep and true joy soothe the soul. In this sacred space, the marvel is achieved: the union of the \nsoul with this sublime energy, which in reality is divine. The practice of Sahaj Marg greatly \nfacilitates progress. This mysterious cocoon of energy transforms the whole being, down to the \nmost secret places of the soul. By virtue of its primary essence, this divine energy can perform \nmiracles. In certain circumstances, everyday life demonstrates this; nothing is insignificant, \nand all is counted. Cultivating love within oneself leads to serenity and total surrender, and \nsubsequently to the best that can be.\nBlessings to all.\nBabuji Maharaj\n\n', 'role': 'system'}, {'content': 'What is true peace?', 'role': 'user'}], 'model': 'gpt-4o', 'n': 1, 'stream': True, 'temperature': 0.0}}
